Beginner level      (Even and odd detection)


                   The following code is an example on switch case that detects even
                   and odd numbers. If the number saved is even a green LED will be
                   ON and if a the saved number is odd then a red LED will be ON




                   Sketch the code


                   int redled=13;                           We will assign an integer variable that has
                   int greenled=11;                         no value to store the remainder of division
                                                            in it.
                   void setup()                             PS: remember when we said 'Variable'(the
                   {                                        drawer) then store a value (the object) in it,
                   pinMode(redled,OUTPUT);                  here we assigned an empty drawer to store
                   pinMode(greenled,OUTPUT);                any integer object in it.
                   Serial.begin(9600);
                   }
                   void loop()
                   {
                     int b;
                     int num=10;


                     if (num%2=w0)
                     {                                      The percentage (%) sign is used here to
                       b=0;                                 check the remainder of dividing num by 2
                     }                                      then store it in variable b.
                                                            If num is even then the remainder is 0 so
                     else if (num%2~w0)                     b=0. If num is odd then the remainder is a
                     {                                      positive value so b = a positive value.
                        b=num%2;
                     }




































