           Level 02 - Arduino - Lesson 03

Intermediate level       (Controlable trac light)


                   We will control the sequence of lighting of 3 LEDS ON and OFF by
                   a speciﬁc data that we will enter in the serial monitor.
                   If we entered letter ”y” a yellow LED is ON, If we entered letter ”g”
                   a Green LED is ON, and If we entered letter ”r” a red LED is ON.


                   Sketch the code


                   int ledr= 2;                             We will assign an empty integer variable
                   int ledg=3;                              (input) that has no value, to store the data
                                                            that we input in serial monitor in it.
                   int ledy= 4;
                   int input;

                   void setup()
                   {
                     Serial.begin(9600);
                     pinMode(ledr, OUTPUT);
                     pinMode(ledg, OUTPUT);
                     pinMode(ledy, OUTPUT);
                   }




                                                                      First we should check if there’s
                   Serial.begin(9600);                                any available space in the serial
                     pinMode(ledr, OUTPUT);                           buffer. If the available space is
                     pinMode(ledg, OUTPUT);                           more than zero then we can
                                                                      input our data.
                     pinMode(ledy, OUTPUT);
                   }
                   void loop()
                                                                      Now let the serial monitor read
                   {                                                  the data that we input through it
                     if (Serial.available() > 0)                      then store the data in the
                     {                                                variable input.
                       input = Serial.read();


                       switch (input)                                 Since we know the speciﬁc
                       {                                              values of input, we will test it
                         case 'y':                                    through switch case.
                           digitalWrite(ledy, HIGH);
                           delay(500);
                          digitalWrite(ledy, LOW);                    In case input =y: Turn yellow LED
                           break;                                     ON for while then OFF.
















           Level 02 - Arduino - Lesson 03

case 'g':                                          In case input =g: Turn green LED
                           digitalWrite(ledg, HIGH);                  ON for while then OFF.
                          delay(500);
                          digitalWrite(ledg, LOW);
                           break;
                                                                      In case input =r: Turn red LED ON
                         case 'r':                                    for while then OFF.
                           digitalWrite(ledr, HIGH);
                          delay(500);
                          digitalWrite(ledr, LOW);
                           break;





                                                                      As a default if none of the
                        default:                                      previous cases is occurred then
                           digitalWrite(ledy, LOW);                   turn all the LEDS OFF
                           digitalWrite(ledg, LOW);
                           digitalWrite(ledr, LOW);
                           break;
                       }
                     }                                                Don’t forget to close all of the
                                                                      loops brackets:
                   }                                                  Switch loop, if condition, then
                                                                      the void loop.











                   After sketching the code


                    1.  Verify the code.

                    2. Connect the circuit as follows.
                        Materials Needed:
                        •  Arduino board and USB cable.
                        •  Breadboard.
                        •  3 Resistors 220 ohm.
                        •  Red, Green, and Yellow LEDS.
















